<HEADLINE> 3 Killed, 24 Injured in Accident in Eastern Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Four vehicles crashed on a Red Sea
highway on Saturday, leaving three people dead and 24 injured,
including 10 Dutch tourists, police officials said.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when a truck, a tourist bus, a mini van
and a car crashed on the highway linking the Red Sea town of
Safaga and the resort of Hurghada, about 415 kilometers southeast
of Cairo, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Details of the crash were not immediately available.
</P>
<P>
The two people in the car, lawmaker Kamal Abu el-Kheir and his
driver, died instantly, said the officials, who spoke on condition
of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
In the mini van, 15 Egyptian workers of an oil company were
injured, one of whom died later in hospital.
</P>
<P>
Ten Dutch tourists, who were in the bus, were injured slightly,
the officials said without elaborating.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of people die every year in road accidents in Egypt,
mainly as a result of speeding.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a trailer rammed into two tourist buses
that were carrying students, killing 31 people and injuring 11
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
