<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill 20 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Two road accidents occurred in Iran
on Friday, killing a total of 20 and injuring another 26,
according to the Islamic News Agency Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Twelve people were killed and 22 injured when a bus run head-on
into a truck trailer in the vicinity of the town of Abadeh in the
southern Fars province.
</P>
<P>
Traffic experts determined the cause of accident, which took
place at 6:00 Friday morning, as veering of the trailer due to
sleepiness of the driver.
</P>
<P>
The trailer's driver was killed on the scene.
</P>
<P>
Another accident happened Friday afternoon when a passenger car
collided with a minibus on the road from northeastern city of
Mashhad to Sabzevar in the northeastern province of Khorasan,
leaving eight people dead and four others injured.
</P>
<P>
Local police blamed the accident, in which seven passengers of
the automobile were killed instantly, on the automobile driver's
negligence in turning too much to the left on the road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
