<HEADLINE> Plane Crash Kills At Least 10 People in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
as a plane carrying passengers on a weekend skydiving trip crashed
early Saturday in Cottrellville Township in Michigan State of the
United States, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which took off from Marine City Airport, broke into
several pieces after it crashed before 9 a.m. (local time), the
reports quoted local officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
State police Trooper Raymond Volosky confirmed the crash later
and said 10 were dead, but he would not confirm the total number
of passengers aboard. A St. Clair County sheriff's dispatcher said
earlier that 10 people were aboard the craft.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the U.S. Federal Aviation Administration and the
National Transportation Safety Board were en route to the scene.
</P>
<P>
Cottrellville Township is located about 65 kilometers north of
Detroit City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
