<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Explanation Can Cover Up Aim of "Two-States"  (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The allegation in Koo's written speech concerning Lee Teng-hui'
s "special state-to-state relations" statement is weak because
this statement radically violates the "one China" principle and
changes the nature of relations across the Straits, the commentary
said.
</P>
<P>
Although Lee did not dare to openly amend the so-called Taiwan
"Constitution" and "Law" immediately, his attempt to split Taiwan
from the motherland is obvious in the "two-states" statement.
</P>
<P>
This destroys the "one China" principle, the basic of stable
development on relations across the Straits, the commentary
pointed out, saying that at the beginning of Lee's government, he
agreed with the "one China" policy. The Taiwan authorities in 1991
specifically defined its policy as one in which both the mainland
and Taiwan are Chinese territory, and a manual published in Taiwan
in 1994 on relations across the Straits insisted on the "one China
" policy, and opposed the ideas of "two Chinas" and "one China,
one Taiwan." According to the manual, relations across the Straits
is an internal issue.
</P>
<P>
Now Lee has failed to keep the faith, changing his words, and
this demonstrate his nature as a deep-rooted separatist, the
commentary noted.
</P>
<P>
Developing relations across the Straits and realizing peaceful
unity can only be based on the "one China" policy. Without this
policy, the interests of Taiwan compatriots and the Chinese nation
will be deeply hurt.
</P>
<P>
Over the past ten year, every time relations across the Straits
became strained or retrogressed, this was a result of Lee's
malicious intent to destroy the "one China" policy. Facts show
that Lee is the biggest stumbling block in the development of
relations across the Straits and China's peaceful unification.
</P>
<P>
According to Koo's written speech, the purpose of Lee's "
special state-to-state relations" statement was to "advance the
level of dialogue" and "establish mechanisms for democracy and
peace." The commentary refuted this as a lie made by Lee to the
Chinese people and the world.
</P>
<P>
Sophism cannot help Lee cover his true nature as a separatist,
the commentary emphasized, noting that people concerned with the
development of relations across the Straits still remember that
Lee repeatedly and deliberately set obstacles in the course of
efforts to improve and develop relations across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
After the Taiwan authorities and SEF refused to conduct
political negotiations with ARATS or implement the common
understanding reached by ARATS and SEF last year, Lee Teng-hui
made his "two states" statement, thus damaging the basis for
dialogue and negotiations between the two sides, the article said.
</P>
<P>
The "two states" statement by Lee Teng-hui has brought about a
tense relationship between the two sides and jeopardized the peace
and stability of the Asian-Pacific Region, adding that he has been
deemed a "troublemaker" by the international community, the
commentary concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
