<HEADLINE> Team Halti Wins Mild Seven Outdoor Quest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALI, China, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Team Halti of Finland won the
Mild Seven Outdoor Quest here on Sunday in Just 23 hours, taking
home the lion's share of the 200,000 U.S. dollars prize money.
</P>
<P>
"The course was much harder than those of last year's," said a
jubilant but exhausted Petri Forsman, who also was a member of the
winning squad in the 1998 race.
</P>
<P>
"And the competition was also much tougher. We had to go harder
than we ever thought possible." he added.
</P>
<P>
Team Eco-Internet finished second, 19 minutes behind Halti in
22:48:48. Team Red Bull-Buff from Spain was third in 23:20:53. All
the teams were forced overcome bad weather in early morning, but
were rewarded with brilliant blue skies and voluptuous white as
they crossed the finish line.
</P>
<P>
Team Mild Seven surprised the field by finishing fourth in the
day's race and climbed from ninth to seventh place overall with a
total time of 23:53:44.
</P>
<P>
The final-day race began with six-kilometer run through a
traditional Bai village at the base of the Gangshan mountains. The
start staggered, so Halti's seven minute overall lead meant they
started exactly seven minutes ahead of the second place finishers,
the Eco-Internet.
</P>
<P>
Eco-Internet pulled even with Halti at the end of the day's
second stage, a 35-kilometer kayak on Lake Er-Hai. But confident
Halti never faltered ascending into the mountains for a two-hour
trail run, that saw athletes clip themselves up to ropes and then
rappel down a 10-meter cliff face the next minutes.
</P>
<P>
The last obstacle for the leading Halti to overcome was a two-
kilometer paddle in Chinese oar boats around Er-Hai before they
sprinted across the finish tape with all the teammates arms in
arms.
</P>
<P>
"The course today was incredibly tough, especially after these
athletes raced so hard for three days previous. Team Halti is to
be commended for such a marvelous performance," race Executive
Director Nick Freyer said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
