<HEADLINE> Gastroenteritis, Diarrhea Claim 27 Lives in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 27 people have died of
gastroenteritis and diarrhea since mid-July, according to reports
of the Kathmandu Post and the official RSS news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Kathmandu Post reported Sunday that 20 people have died of
diarrhea in Baglung and Gulmi districts in western Nepal since
mid-July.
</P>
<P>
RSS said that gastroenteritis has claimed seven lives in
Dailekh district in mid-western Nepal so far since the rainy
season.
</P>
<P>
Gastroenteritis and diarrhea are common diseases in Nepal,
breaking out even more frequently in the rainy season which lasts
from June to September. More than 1,000 people die of various
diseases every year, including gastroenteritis and diarrhea.
</P>
</TEXT>
