<HEADLINE> Lim Kim San to Act as President of Singapore for 2 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Lim Kim San, chairman of the
Council of Singapore's Presidential Advisers, will be the
country's acting president on August 2 and 3 in view of President
Ong Teng Cheong's bereavement of his wife of 36 years, according
to a press statement from the Prime Minister's Office.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Ong, the country's first lady, passed away Friday after a
two-and-a-half year battle with cancer and her funeral will be
held Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday and Sunday, hundreds of Singaporeans, government
officials and foreign dignitaries and diplomats went to the
president's private residence to extend their condolences.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong and Mrs. Goh, Senior
Minister Lee Kuan Yew and Mrs. Lee, Deputy Prime Minister Lee
Hsien Loong and his wife were among those who conveyed their
condolences at the wake at the president's home Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Mauritius President Cassam Uteem and his wife paid
their last respects the same day.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Chen Baoliu called on the family Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Born Ling Siew May in Shanghai, China, in 1937, the fourth
child in a family of six, she married Mr. Ong in 1963, the year
she graduated from the University of Adelaide in Australia with an
architecture degree. They have two sons. 
</P>
