<HEADLINE> Voelker Sets World Record in 50-meter Backstroke </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Sandra Voelker rewrote
her own world record to win the women's 50 meters backstroke title
and her second individual gold medal on the final day of the
European championships on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Voelker, winner of the 100 meters backstroke on Friday, timed
28.71 seconds for the one-length sprint to beat the listed world
mark of 28.78 she set in Monaco in June.
</P>
<P>
Voelker quickly established a lead and never let anyone close
enough to make a serious challenge.
</P>
<P>
Former Russian Nina Zhivanevskaya, who now swims for Spain,
clocked 29.02 to take the silver as she had in the 100 event.
</P>
<P>
Metka Sparavec was third with the bronze, the first for
Slovenia, in 29.25. 
