<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Sees 13 Percent Rise In Half-Year Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province has
reported a 12.7 percent year-on-year rise in foreign trade, to 13.
39 billion US dollars-worth during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The total includes 7.73 billion US dollars-worth of exports and
5.66 billion US dollars-worth of imports.
</P>
<P>
Exports from local state-run enterprises reached 3.16 billion
US dollars-worth during the half-year period, a 4.5 percent rise
on a yearly basis, with the volume accounted for by overseas-
funded enterprises growing by 20 percent to 4.2 billion US dollars-
worth, and the volume accounted for by private businesses
rocketing by 580 percent to 3.38 million US dollars-worth.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Asia have resumed their former level, reaching 3.88
billion US dollars-worth during the six-month period, a rise of 14.
4 percent on a yearly basis, with exports to North America
climbing 26 percent, and to Australia, 37.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The province has further optimized its export mix, exporting 2.
19 billion US dollars-worth of machinery, and of electrical, audio
and visual goods during the first half of the year, a 24 percent
rise on a yearly basis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
