said China enjoys the company's confidence as an important place
for marketing and development.
</P>
<P>
Allied Signal Co. of the U.S. is one of the 30 companies which
comprise the Dow Jones Industrial Index. The American magazine
Fortune has twice chosen the company as the best aviation industry
company in the U.S..
</P>
<P>
"We are confident about the Asia-Pacific region, despite the
impact of the Asian economic crisis," Yuen said here recently. "
China has seen its economy boom in recent years, which is
important to us. We are seeking collaborators inside China to
build a steady basis for future development by combining our
specialties with China's advantages."
</P>
<P>
He added that he hoped that China would continue to adopt
stable policies, and never stop developing. He said that he
believed that after overcoming the difficulties cropping up in the
process of the ongoing reforms, China will resume stable
development in 2003, when even more foreign investment is expected
to pour into the country.
</P>
<P>
Allied Signal Co. entered China in 1994, with only 20 staff;
now it has 13 branch companies in Shanghai, Guangzhou, Suzhou and
Nanjing on a solely-owned and cooperative basis. And the number of
staff has increased to more than 1,000, while the investment has
topped 300 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Yuen said that the company will focus on the engineering,
electrical and chemicals sectors in the near future.
</P>
<P>
