<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.7 on
the Richer scale Sunday rattled Dolakha district in central Nepal,
about 100 kilometers northeast of Kathmandu, according to Madhav
Raj Panday, senior officer of the Department of Mines and Geology.
</P>
<P>
The tremor struck at 14:10 local time.
</P>
<P>
