<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Exports 5.3 Billion Dollars in 1998-99 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh exported goods worth 5.3
billion U.S. dollars during the 1998-99 fiscal year ending June 30
this year, Commerce and Industries Minister Tofail Ahmed said here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The figure registered a growth of 2.7 percent in value compared
with that of the previous year, and a shortfall of 5.4 percent for
the target of 5.6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The country's exports stood at 5.16 billion dollars in fiscal
1997-98, 4.42 billion dollars in 1996-97 and 3.8 billion dollars
in 1995-96, the minister told reporters at the conference room of
the Commerce Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Despite global economic meltdown and nearly-three-month-long
devastating floods, the country's export performance in the last
fiscal was quite satisfactory in terms of growth and target, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the shortfall of 300 million dollars in the
target to global recession and financial losses inflicted by
floods hitting the country in 1998. "We could export only nine
months in the last fiscal due to devastating floods," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
