<HEADLINE> hke080114-Afghan Taliban Consolidate Positions at Bagram Air Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban have
consolidated the positions at the strategic Bagram air base which
they captured Saturday night from the opposition Northern Alliance
forces.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban forces captured the Bagram air base and the
surrounding heights Saturday night and now they are consolidating
the positions, Taliban chief representative to Islamabad
Saeed-ur-Rahman Haqqani told Xinhua Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Bagram air base is located in Parwan province, 50
kilometers northeast of capital Kabul. It is just outside the
Panjsher valley stronghold of opposition commander Ahmad Shah
Masood.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban fighters have also captured intersection outside
the Bagram air base. They launched attacks from Shakardara and
Guldara and entered Qarahbagh district before overrunning Bagram,
said reports reaching here from Kabul Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that about 200 people, including 17 Taliban
fighters, have been killed while a large number of others injured.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban launched their large-scale summer offensive against
the Masood-led opposition on Wednesday, and are now planning to
advance towards the northeastern Panjsher valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
