<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Commercial Bank of Zimbabwe
has raised 85 million U.S. dollars from a number of international
banks over the past few months to support the country's exports
and imports despite the down rating Zimbabwe has received by most
overseas banks, The Sunday Mail reported.
</P>
