<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to witness millennium's Last Solar Eclipse in Aug. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Central India will plunge into
a total darkness on August 11 when the millennium's last total
solar eclipse (TSE) takes place, according to M.P. Birla
Planetarium in Calcutta.
</P>
<P>
Just around sunset, India will be wrapped by a ribbon of
darkness for about a minute as the moon's shadow will cast an
80-km wide shadow from Gujarat in the west to Andhra Pradesh in
the east.
</P>
<P>
The last TSE was visible from India on October 24, 1995.
</P>
<P>
This time the eclipse will be visible in India on the western
coast at 17:58 standard Indian time. It is estimated to leave the
bay of Bengal coast at 18:06. 
</P>
</TEXT>
