<HEADLINE> WB Loans Introduced for Embankment Reinforcement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Starting this year, central
China's Hunan Province will introduce 70 million U.S. dollars of
loans from the World Bank (WB) to reinforce the provincial section
of embankment of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
It is part of local anti-flood efforts and the money will be
used for consolidating 142 km of dykes and dams. 
