<HEADLINE> Private Sector Economy Grows in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The total number of private
businesses in east China's Jiangsu Province, one of the country's
economic powerhouses, grew 22 percent on a year-on-year basis in
the first half of this year, to top 1.65 million.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises, with combined registered capital of 73.5
billion yuan, employ more than four million people.
</P>
<P>
An official of the provincial government said that Jiangsu has
taken a series of measures as part of a national effort to boost
the private sector of the economy over the past few years, such as
the relaxing restrictions for loans and encouraging private firms
to participate in restructuring state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A number of industrial development zones have also been
established for private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period of this year, these enterprises
achieved 80.2 billion yuan in output value and over 101 billion
yuan in sales.
</P>
<P>
About 7,000 private firms in the province have been engaged in
scientific and technological development, many of whom have gained
a share in the international market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
