<HEADLINE> Xie Leads Galliamova at World Women's Chess Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAZAN, RUSSIA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Xie Jun of China beat
Russian Alisa Galliamova at the second game of the world women's
chess championship at Kosan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Xie, who was held to a tie by Galliamova at the opening game on
Friday, sealed the victory at the 29th move after Galliamova made
a lethal mistake in the 23rd move and lost her rhythm for falling
short of time.
</P>
<P>
The championship, which is shared by China and Russia, will
have its first eight games from July 29 to August 9 here and the
next eight games from August 13 to 25 at Shengyang in the
Northeast of China.
</P>
<P>
As is regulated by the FIDE, the chess world ruling body,
either player who first collected 8.5 points will be the winner
and the play-off is needed if both sides tie 8-all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
