<HEADLINE> EDS-More Added Highlights of Major Beijing-based Newspapers (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 Liberation Army Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Today's editorial to mark the 72nd anniversary of the People
's Liberation Army (PLA) said the PLA, under the absolute
leadership of the Communist Party of China, is an army armed with
scientific theory, a strong pillar of the people's democratic
dictatorship, an iron great wall for protecting the socialist
motherland, and an invincible force that can be trusted by the
Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
The 72nd anniversary of the PLA came at an unusual time, with
the Army facing both opportunities and challenges, as well as
hopes and difficulties, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo crisis shows that the world is not peaceful and
tranquil and that war is not a distant issue. Lee Teng-hui's
recent remarks on so-called "special state-to-state relations"
have aroused China's serious concern about the separatist force on
the Taiwan island. And the case of the Falun Gong cult, an illegal
organization, has set a serious task for the army to maintain
social stability.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that in short, the Army has two basic tasks:
to win in every battle and to maintain its true quality.
</P>
<P>
It expressed the Army's determination to continue to take Mao
Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping's military thinking as its guide
and comprehensively carry out President Jiang Zemin's instructions
on army building.
</P>
<P>
People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) reached its goal
of downsizing the army by 500,000 last year, according to Chinese
Defense Minister Chi Haotian.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, vice chairman of the
Central Military Commission, and state councilor, made the remarks
during a reception yesterday marking the 72nd anniversary of the
PLA.
</P>
<P>
-- The newspaper carried a special commentary today co-written
by the newspaper and Xinhua News Agency to reiterate that China
will not accept the attempt by Lee Teng-hui to separate Taiwan
from China with the statement of "special state-to-state relations.
"
</P>
<P>
It said that a written speech by Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF), on July 30, which not only
repeated Lee's "two states" statement but also added the words "
fully reflecting the will of people in Taiwan," totally violates
the agreement on "one China" principle already reached by both
sides of the Taiwan Straits in 1992, and was of course rejected by
the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Officials and people from all walks of life in China
yesterday refuted the fatalistic philosophy propagated by the
Falun Gong cult, an illegal organization, and vowed their
determination to build a scientific philosophy to conquer
ignorance and superstition.
</P>
<P>
 Business Weekly of China Daily
</P>
<P>
--China's auditors are urged to develop sharper eyes to comply
with or benefit from new rules of responsibility under
consideration at the National Audit Office.
</P>
<P>
Auditor-General Li Jinhua said that the office is working on a
new auditing system, which includes auditing principles,
regulations concerning incentives for auditors and rules of
responsibility to improve the quality of audits. 
