<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Police Seizes 400 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Police seized some 400 kilograms
of cocaine Friday in a truck in southern Nicaragua, the newspaper
La Prensa said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The drug, which is the biggest amount ever found this year in
the country, was detected when the police were making a routine
inspection of a truck that came from Costa Rica bound for Managua,
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The car's Costa Rican owner and his Nicaraguan assistant have
been detained.
</P>
<P>
The drug was contained in 13 bags and hidden under tons of
bananas that allegedly would be sold in the city.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, some 210 kilograms of
cocaine were seized, police said. 
