<HEADLINE> Uruguayan, Argentine Presidents to Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan President Julio Maria
Sanguinetti will meet with his Argentine counterpart Carlos Menem
in Buenos Aires Sunday to review the progress of the South
American Common Market (Mercosur).
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti, Mercosur's present president, will go to Argentina
to watch the soccer game between River Plane and Penarol, Uruguay'
s presidential office said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
His meeting with Menem has come after he phoned several times
Argentine and Brazilian presidents to urge them to discuss the
bloc's crisis caused by a trade conflict between Argentina and
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Recession-hit Argentina had taken unilateral measures to head
off a series of Brazilian exports made cheaper by Brazil's sharp
real devaluation in January. The move triggered the worst
bickering between the two countries since Mercosur began working
as a customs union in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Sanguinetti held that the Argentine decision to cancel trade
safeguards among Mercosur members "prepared the way" to
negotiating "in a better climate."
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, which groups Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay and Paraguay
with Chile and Bolivia as associates, will hold here on August 4
an extraordinary meeting to study the progress of the group.
</P>
