<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Host ASEAN Tourism Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar will host the 10th meeting
of National Tourism Organizations (NTO) of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on August 24-26, according to an
official announcement here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN is making efforts to restore the vibrancy of the tourism
industry. At its second meeting held in Singapore in January this
year, ASEAN ministers agreed to launch a Visit ASEAN Millennium
Year with focus on international travel and tourism in the ASEAN
region.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to promote eco-tourism and cruise tourism
program, and to establish a network among ASEAN Tourism Training
Centers with emphasis on new job skills and new technologies in
tourism policy and planning.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 292,282 foreign
tourists visited Myanmar in 1998-99, of them tourists from other
ASEAN countries accounted for 5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
