<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombian Crude Output Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's crude
production averaged 830,000 barrels a day in the first half of
the year, up almost 100,000 barrels compared with the average of
last year.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release published Saturday by the Empresa
de Petroleo de Colombia (Ecopetrol) oil company, the crude output
in June hit 835,000 barrels a day.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas output in the country averaged 480 million cubic
feet per day.
</P>
<P>
Petrol exports at the end of June produced a trade surplus of
more than 800 million U.S. dollars, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Imports, mainly of gasoline, during the period exceeded 2.7
million barrels in volume and 52.7 million dollars in value.
</P>
</TEXT>
