<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Namibia Defeats South Africa again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Namibia continued the run of giant-
killing upsets in this year's Cosafa Castle Cup, defeating South
Africa on penalties in their quarter-final match in Windhoek,
Namibia on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Namibia won 4-1 on kicks after a 1-1 draw, just two weeks after
lowly-ranked Swaziland had beaten Zimbabwe in the same tournament.
</P>
<P>
It was also the second successive year that South Africa had
lost to their northern neighbours in the annual southern African
championship.
</P>
<P>
South Africa led in the first half with a goal from Pollen
Ndlanya, forcefully heading home from a corner kick in the 32nd
minute.
</P>
<P>
Namibia's equaliser also came from a corner with Johannes
Hindjou getting a close-range touch-in in the 50th minute.
</P>
<P>
The win means Namibia join Swaziland and Angola in the last
four with Zambia still to play Mozambique in the last quarter-
final match on August 7.
</P>
<P>
The draw for the semi-finals of the competition was due to be
made later on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
