<HEADLINE> Sampras Returns to Top Ranking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- American Pete Sampras reclaimed
the world number one ranking for a record 271st week Saturday as
he reached the final of the Los Angeles Open Tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sampras eased to a 6-0, 6-2 victory over 236th-ranked
Australian James Sekulov on Saturday to replace Australian Pat
Rafter at the top spot when the new ATP Tour rankings are released
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, 27, who has had 12 grand slam singles titles under his
belt, needs just one more to surpass the record set by Roy Emerson.
</P>
</TEXT>
