<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Larsen Takes Lead in Pan Am women's Modern Pentathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Mary Beth Larsen leads
the first-ever Pan American Games women's modern pentathlon after
two events.
</P>
<P>
Larsen had an outstanding fencing round, winning 21 of 27 bouts
to score 1,068 points and move up from a sixth-place standing
after the pistol competition. She leads Mexico's Maria Ortega by
44 points in a tight race that has eight of the 10 pentathletes
within 234 points of the lead.
</P>
<P>
Like Larsen, teammate Samantha Harvey recovered from a low-
scoring shooting performance to move into medal contention. Harvey
won 17 fencing bouts and is in fifth place after a succcessful
shooting round was penalized 200 points because her pistol failed
a weight test.
</P>
<P>
The modern pentathlon resumes with men's and women's swimming
afterwards. Riding and running will follow, with the pentathlon
scheduled to be completed at approximately 7:30 this evening.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
