<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuba, Brazil Set up Women's Volleyball Final at Pan Am </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The stage is set for a
Cuba-Brazil showdown for gold in the Pan Am women's volleyball
final tomorrow night.
</P>
<P>
Cuba swept the United States 25-20, 25-21, 25-23 in the first
semi-final last night, followed by Brazil beating the surprise
semifinalists the Dominican Republic 25-20, 25-13, 25-12 at the
Winnipeg Arena.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Dominican will battle it out for the
bronze also tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Cuba, gold medallists at the last two Olympics and world
championships, is considered the most powerful team in the world.
</P>
<P>
The team on the floor here yesterday was basically the same
team that won the 1998 World Championship in Japan, with the
exception of the best player in the world, Regla Torres, who is
still recovering from a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
The hosts Canada, otherwise enjoying a great Games so far, hadn
't fared well in the women's volleyball. They ended their
tournament yesterday by posting its first victory, beating Peru to
place fifth in the six-team tournament.
</P>
<P>
The men's semi-finals go head-to-head today at the Winnipeg
Arena where Cuba faces Argentina and Canada takes on Brazil.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
