<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Beats Senegal 2:1 in Africa Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe national soccer team,
The Warriors Saturday beat Seneral 2:1 in a crucial Africa Cup of
Nations qualifier at the National Sports Stadium in Harare.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe's goals came from European-based professionals, Peter
Ndlovu in the eighth minute and Agent Sawu in the 55th minute and
Senegal pulled one back in the 77th minute.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe now leads the three-team play-off group created after
Zimbabwe was disqualified from hosting the continental soccer
tournament next year and replaced by co-hosts Ghana and Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The play-off group has Zimbabwe, Senegal and Eritrea. Zimbabwe
has six points after winning against Senegal on Saturday and
Eritrea two weeks earlier.
</P>
<P>
Senegal has three points for beating Eritrea and losing to
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
The winner in the group will qualify to play in the Cup finals
in February.  
</P>
</TEXT>
