<HEADLINE> Costa Edges Top Seed Kafelnikov to Enter Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Albert Costa of
Spain defeated top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia 7-6, 6-2 in
the Generali Open tennis Tournament in Kitzbuehel on Saturday to
set up an all-Spanish final.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Fernando Vicente eliminated Austrian Stefan Koubek 6-4,
6-4 in the other semi-final.
</P>
<P>
Costa, also a winner in Kitzbuehel in 1995 and who has yet to
lose a match on the clay at Kitzbuehel, slugged it out from the
baseline and frequently outwitted Kafelnikov with deceptive drop
shots.
</P>
<P>
Costa, whose victory took his winning streak at Kitzbuehel to
14, has won all his 10 ATP titles on clay.
</P>
<P>
Vicente, the 13th seed, overcame a faltering serve in the first
set to break Austrian number one Koubek in the ninth game.
</P>
<P>
The Spaniard shifted up a gear in the second set and took
advantage of numerous unforced errors by his opponent to again
break in the ninth game and serve out for the match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
