<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, August 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Saturday urged
Congress to pass the Patients' bill of rights to expand patients'
right under managed health care plans before Congress starts a
long August recess.
</P>
<P>
"The American people sent us to Washington to get work done,
and Congress shouldn't go on summer vacation without voting on the
patient's bill of rights," Clinton said in his weekly radio
address. (Clinton-Congress-Patients Bill)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa Saturday called
for regional economic integration to protect the collective
interests in the process of globalization.
</P>
<P>
Opening the 73rd Zambia agricultural and commercial show here,
Mkapa said his country "attaches great importance to regional
economic integration as a vehicle of our economic liberation. It
is also an important mechanism of protecting our collective
interests in the process of globalization."  (Zambia-Regional
Integration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- Morocco's new king, Mohammed VI, has promised to
pursue the political reform engaged by his father, King Hassan II,
through adopting political pluralism under a constitutional
monarchy.
</P>
<P>
