<HEADLINE> Italy Urges Serbian Role in Balkan Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Deputy Prime Minister Sergio
Mattarella confirmed Saturday that the Italian government wants
the Serbian people involved in material and political
reconstruction in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Mattarella was speaking at a conference in Italy's northeast
city of Udine, organized by Caritas, a Catholic charity
organization.
</P>
<P>
Echoing Prime Minister Massimo D'Alema after Friday's Sarajevo
summit for a Balkans stability pact, he said reconstruction would
be "insufficient and probably ineffective" without Serbian
involvement.
</P>
<P>
He said that Italy could expect to play a major role in Balkan
reconstruction, not just because of geographical vicinity, but
also because of Italy's "close dialogue" with the Balkan
countries.
</P>
<P>
But he also denied that Italy has a pro-Serb stance, saying,
"We distinguish the Serbian government, with its very grave
responsibilities, from the Serbian people, which must pay for its
government's mistakes."
</P>
<P>
According to the deputy premier, in the near future, Serbia
must give itself a government which is "more democratic, more
credible internationally and more respectful of human rights."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
